comment:
* Handle to an enqueued transcoding operation. An instance of this class represents a single
     * enqueued transcoding operation. The caller can use that instance to query the status or
     * progress, and to get the result once the operation has completed.

variables.name: STATUS_PENDING
variables.comment: The job is enqueued but not yet running.

variables.name: RESULT_NONE
variables.comment: The job does not have a result yet.

variables.name: RESULT_ERROR
variables.comment: The job encountered an error while running.

variables.name: RESULT_CANCELED
variables.comment: The job was canceled by the caller.

methods.name: public void setOnProgressChangedListener(@NonNull @CallbackExecutor Executor executor, @Nullable OnProgressChangedListener listener)
methods.comment:
* Set a progress listener.
         * @param listener The progress listener.

methods.name: public void cancel()
methods.comment:
* Cancels the transcoding job and notify the listener. If the job happened to finish before
         * being canceled this call is effectively a no-op and will not update the result in that
         * case.

methods.name: public float getProgress()
methods.comment:
* Gets the progress of the transcoding job. The progress is between 0 and 1, where 0 means
         * that the job has not yet started and 1 means that it is finished.
         * @return The progress.

methods.name: public int getStatus()
methods.comment:
* Gets the status of the transcoding job.
         * @return The status.

methods.name: public int getResult()
methods.comment:
* Gets the result of the transcoding job.
         * @return The result.

methods.name: private void processJobEvent(@Event int event, int arg)

methodNames: public void setOnProgressChangedListener(@NonNull @CallbackExecutor Executor executor, @Nullable OnProgressChangedListener listener)
private void processJobEvent(@Event int event, int arg)
